<paper id="1584975026"><title>Breaking Public Key Cryptosystems on Tamper Resistant Devices in the Presence of Transient Faults</title><year>1997</year><authors><author org="National University of Singapore" id="2924724599">Feng Bao</author><author org="National University of Singapore" id="2062283694">Robert H. Deng</author><author org="National University of Singapore" id="2630090033">Yongfei Han</author><author org="National University of Singapore" id="2165292187">Albert B. Jeng</author><author org="National University of Singapore" id="682632610">A. Desai Narasimhalu</author><author org="National University of Singapore" id="2052788744">Teow-Hin Ngair</author></authors><n_citation>124</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1996360405</reference><reference>2095708839</reference><reference>2108834246</reference></references><venue id="1184048318" type="C">International Workshop on Security</venue><doi>10.1007/BFb0028164</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.38754">Internet privacy</keyword><keyword weight="0.41655">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.4384">Computer security</keyword><keyword weight="0.50715">Network security</keyword><keyword weight="0.52711">Smart card</keyword><keyword weight="0.42318">Computer network</keyword><keyword weight="0.51675">Cryptosystem</keyword><keyword weight="0.56165">Digital Signature Algorithm</keyword><keyword weight="0.57542">Tamper resistance</keyword><keyword weight="0.54431">PKCS</keyword><keyword weight="0.58038">Public-key cryptography</keyword><keyword weight="0.65093">Schnorr signature</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>In this paper we present a method of attacking public-key cryptosystems (PKCs) on tamper resistant devices. The attack makes use of transient faults and seems applicable to many types of PKCs. In particular, we show how to attack the RSA, the EIGamal signature scheme, the Schnorr signature scheme, and the DSA. We also present some possible methods to counter the attack.</abstract></paper>